Here’s the missing high-signal stuff written in your note style, keeping your tone/structure.

Consciousness:

consciousness in nanavira sense is not a little observer inside experience, it is the presence of the phenomenon itself. not red + consciousness as two things, but red-present. the red is the percept / quality, consciousness is the fact of its presence.

you can’t find consciousness as an object because anything you find is another phenomenon consciousness is of. consciousness of awareness usually means consciousness of a subtle sign called awareness / spaciousness / clarity / knowingness.

no phenomena = no consciousness of phenomena. consciousness is always consciousness of something, it has an object/support. this avoids turning consciousness into an eternal witness/self.

nanananda is less “consciousness = presence” and more “consciousness establishes itself on name-and-form.” consciousness gets footing in signs, concepts, feelings, body/world, and then the self-world spins.

cessation of consciousness does not mean blankness or no experience while alive. it means cessation of prepared / established / ignorance-conditioned consciousness, consciousness that has footing in name-and-form as me, mine, my world.

the arahant can still see phone as phone, but phone does not become my phone / my escape / my validation / my world. concept remains but bondage to concept stops.

Name-and-form:

name-and-form is the structured world of experience, the thing as meaningful and embodied: perception, feeling, intention, attention, contact + form. not raw data but experience already organized.

consciousness and name-and-form lean on each other like two sheaves of reeds. no conscious presence without some phenomenon, no phenomenon-as-experienced without consciousness.

phone-as-experienced is not just a physical object. it is colour, shape, recognition, use, memory, feeling, intention, craving, ownership, world. phone is a node in name-and-form.

Papañca:

papanca is the expansion from sign into story, world, self, other, time, fate. the tiny cue becomes a universe.

flat tone becomes rejection, rejection becomes they see the real me, this becomes i am defective, this becomes i need to become pleasing, this becomes the role.

papanca is how the movie gets plot. it adds past, future, comparison, status, blame, strategy, identity.

the sign is the spark, papanca is the forest fire.

Ignorance:

ignorance is not not knowing facts, it is not seeing the conditional construction of the present self-world.

it is taking the interpreted appearance as simply real, taking feeling as my problem, taking signs as evidence, taking the born role as who i am.

non-ignorance is not thinking “everything is dependent” all day. it is catching the chain live: this is contact, this is feeling, this is sign, this is craving, this is becoming.

seeing = the self-world is seen as being assembled while it is being assembled.

Vedanā:

vedana is the first charge of experience, pleasant / unpleasant / neutral. not yet full emotion, but the seed of movement.

craving is the organism’s movement around vedana: towards pleasant, away from unpleasant, around neutral through distraction / certainty / becoming.

self is born when vedana is appropriated: this is not just unpleasant, this is happening to me and must be solved by me.

trauma is where certain vedanas became unbearable, so the organism learned to birth roles very fast in order to manage them.

Craving / grasping / becoming:

craving = movement to resolve the charge.

grasping = taking the sign/story/strategy as mine and real.

becoming = the mode of existence that forms around the strategy.

birth = speaking, acting, perceiving as that role.

kamma = action from the role that reinforces the world in which the role seems necessary.

the role is not random, it is a solution to vedana. the issue is that the solution becomes identity.

Trauma:

trauma is old dependent arising with extreme weight. a contact/feeling that could not be processed became a survival formation.

fragmentation = a self-mode was born to hold what could not be felt directly.

reenactment = the nervous system returns to familiar signs because it knows how to survive them, hoping for resolution but usually reinforcing the same world.

healing = the old feeling is contacted with enough safety that the old role does not need to take over.

dhamma + trauma: trauma explains why the sign has so much charge, dhamma shows how the charge becomes self right now.

Narcissism / shame:

shame is unpleasant vedana plus self-view: not “something feels bad” but “i am bad / exposed / wrong.”

vulnerable narcissism is when shame births the wounded-special self. the role says see me, understand me, recognise my depth, don’t expose my ordinariness.

grandiosity and collapse are both strategies around shame. superior one and defective one are both selfing.

antidote is not humiliation or self-hate. it is feeling shame without becoming special, wounded, superior, misunderstood or defective.

ordinary shame, ordinary need, ordinary hurt, ordinary being — felt without turning it into mythology.

Predictive processing:

sankhara is like priors / weights / precision / action policies, but dhamma is deeper because it asks why the model is appropriated as me.

the organism predicts a world and acts to reduce uncertainty, but craving turns uncertainty into a self-problem.

dhamma reduces the need to create a self around uncertainty.

freedom is first increased options, then seeing the option-maker as conditioned too.

Hoffman / Kastrup / Seth / Friston:

seth = the world-self is controlled hallucination generated by embodied prediction.

friston = organism acts to maintain itself by reducing uncertainty / prediction error.

hoffman = perception is interface icons, not reality as it is.

kastrup = consciousness / experience is the ground, matter is what mind looks like from outside.

dhamma does not need to settle the metaphysics. even “consciousness is the ground” can become a sign. the practical question is where consciousness is establishing, what sign is being grasped, what craving is fuelling becoming.

Steiner vs Nanavira:

steiner wants free spiritual individuality through conscious thinking. unfree action is action from instinct, habit, past conditioning.

nanavira asks whether the free thinker is another refined self-view.

steiner = become conscious enough to act from intuition rather than conditioning.

nanavira = see even the actor / chooser / spiritual individual as dependently arisen and not self.

Mamoo:

the self is a role born to resolve a charge.

the world you inhabit is conditioned by the kind of being being generated.

the fawner inhabits a world of dangerous moods.

the ashamed one inhabits a world of exposure.

the narcissist inhabits a world of mirrors.

the seeker inhabits a world of lack and completion.

cessation is when feeling can be known without casting a self to solve it.
